children.subject: I definitely want to take 170 asap, I guess I'm wondering more whether I should swap 120 with 170 or 161 with 170.

I would just keep the current schedule you have because 170 is a class that is typically offered every semester -- so if the schedule works and you dont have any urgency in terms of taking 170, just wait until next semester.
I would argue that 170 can be put off just because OP notes how interested they are in the content of 120.
I think you should take 170 asap. The course will be webcasted so I don't think the lecture time really matters.

history.content: 170 is normally webcasted and 120 with Babak normally is, so as long as exam overlap doesn't happen you'll be fine. When I took with Babak, we had a "midterm 3" the last lecture instead of a final during the final timeslot, so it worked out for me

Currently, I am enrolled in EE120, CS161, and CS188 for next semester. As CS170 is now open, I was thinking of switching out 161 with 170, but there is a conflict with EE120. 

Should I switch with 120 instead? I usually go to most all lectures and are not used to webcasting, which I would have to do for 170. However, I want to get 120 done as soon as possible because I am very interested in the topics / future classes in that area. 

Edit: It seems as if the final exam times for EE120 and CS170 do conflict-- should I expect to see a midterm 3 instead of a final?
